# ReMA — Remote Machine Access

Execute commands on remote machines through a shared mount. All machines must mount the same data volume.

## Prerequisites

- `REMA_DIR` environment variable must be set (via `~/.rema_config`, which is created by `install.sh`)
- To activate: `source ~/.rema_config` or `source ~/.bashrc` (if added during install)
- Remote machine must have a worker running (`rema start <name>`)

## Quick Reference

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `rema start <name>` | Start worker in current directory |
| `rema stop <name>` | Stop worker |
| `rema status <name>` | idle / busy / off |
| `rema run <name> [--async] -- <cmd>` | Execute command (sync: real-time; async: immediate return) |
| `rema log <name>` | Show latest job output |
| `rema log <name> <job_id>` | Show specific job output |
| `rema list` | Show all machines and status |
| `rema rm <name>` | Remove a machine (must be off) |

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Disapole-Xiao/ReMA.git
cd ReMA
cd /your/shared/workspace   # .rema/ will be created here
bash install.sh
source ~/.bashrc
```

To uninstall: `bash uninstall.sh`

## Usage

Before running commands, the remote machine must have a worker running:
```bash
# On remote machine, in the desired working directory:
cd /your/project
rema start <name>
```

Then from any machine:
```bash
# Check status
rema status <name>

# Run command (sync, real-time output, same exit code as command)
rema run <name> -- nvidia-smi
rema run <name> -- "cd project && python train.py"

# Run command (async, returns immediately, retrieve with log)
rema run <name> --async -- "sleep 10 && python train.py"

# Check output of async job (latest or by ID)
rema log <name>
rema log <name> <job_id>

# List all machines
rema list

# Remove a machine (must be off — stop first if idle/busy)
rema stop <name>
rema rm <name>
```

## Configuration

Set via `~/.rema_config` or environment variable. Priority: env var > `~/.rema_config` > default.

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `REMA_DIR` | required | Shared directory path (auto-set by `install.sh`) |
| `REMA_LOG_KEEP_DAYS` | `7` | Auto-delete old logs (days) |

To change log retention: `echo 'export REMA_LOG_KEEP_DAYS=30' >> ~/.rema_config && source ~/.rema_config`

## Key Behaviors

- Commands execute in the directory where `rema start` was run
- Sync mode returns the same exit code as the command
- `rema list` shows all registered machines; `off` means worker is not running or heartbeat expired
- Each job gets a unique ID; use `rema log <name> <job_id>` for specific jobs
- To remove a machine, it must be `off` — run `rema stop` first if idle/busy
- Multiple workers can run on the same machine under different names
